The inflation rate in Zimbabwe is well over 200%. President Emmerson Mnangagwa's Zanu-PF government has not been able to achieve economic stability, despite instituting some reforms. 

He has also been accused of widespread human rights abuses in South Africa's northern neighbour - forcing even more Zimbabweans to try and seek a better life in South Africa. 

Michelle Bachelet was giving her global human rights overview during the opening session of the 42nd Human Rights Council in Geneva.

--UN--